title: 15-year-old girl killed in Davenport shooting
content:
DAVENPORT, Iowa (WQAD) -- A 15-year-old Davenport girl is dead after an overnight shooting.
Police say Ayana Culbreath, 15, was shot shortly after midnight on Sunday, June 26, 2016.
Officers were called to the 4200 block of Warren Street around 12:30 a.m. They found Culbreath, and medics transported her to Genesis East Medical Center for treatment. She was pronounced dead shortly after arrival.
Shell casings were also located at the scene.
Detectives are still investigating the shooting.
